The paper deals with the application of machine learning models to predict SLA violations in cloud computing, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of SLA in cloud systems, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of re-sampling methods to overcome the challenge of imbalanced data, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE) and cybersecurity (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different machine learning models, which is related to the field of machine learning (cs.LG).
